Name: AccountDescriptiveName
Notes: The descriptive name of the Customer account.

Name: AdGroupCount
Notes: The count of AdGroup objects using the bidding strategy.

Name: AdGroupCriteriaCount
Notes: The count of AdGroupCriterion objects using the bidding strategy or label.

Name: AllConversionRate
Notes: AllConversions divided by total clicks that can be conversion-tracked. This is how often a click on your ad resulted in a conversion. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversions
Notes: Best estimate of the total number of conversions that AdWords drives. Includes website, cross-device, and phone call conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AllConversionValue
Notes: The total value of all of your conversions, including those that are estimated. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: AverageCpc
Notes: The total cost of all clicks divided by the total number of clicks received.

Name: AverageCpm
Notes: Average Cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM).

Name: AveragePosition
Notes: Your ad's position relative to those of other advertisers. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: CampaignCount
Notes: The count of Campaign objects using the bidding strategy.

Name: Clicks
Notes: The number of clicks.

Name: ConversionRate
Notes: The number of conversions divided by total clicks that can be tracked to conversions. Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Conversions
Notes: The number of conversions for all conversion actions that you have opted into optimization. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ConversionValue
Notes: The sum of conversion values for all conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Cost
Notes: The sum of your cost-per-click (CPC) and cost-per-thousand impressions (CPM) costs during this period.

Name: CostPerAllConversion
Notes: Total cost divided by all conversions.

Name: CostPerConversion
Notes: The Cost attributable to conversion-tracked clicks divided by the number of conversions

Name: CrossDeviceConversions
Notes: Conversions from when a customer clicks on an AdWords ad on one device, then converts on a different device or browser. Cross-device conversions are already included in your AllConversions column. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Ctr
Notes: The number of clicks your ad receives (Clicks) divided by the number of times your ad is shown (Impressions). Percentage returned as "x.xx%". To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: Date
Notes: The date formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: DayOfWeek
Enum Values:
MONDAY / Monday
TUESDAY / Tuesday
WEDNESDAY / Wednesday
THURSDAY / Thursday
FRIDAY / Friday
SATURDAY / Saturday
SUNDAY / Sunday
Notes: The name of the day of the week, e.g., "Monday".

Name: Device
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
DESKTOP / Computers
HIGH_END_MOBILE / Mobile devices with full browsers
TABLET / Tablets with full browsers
Notes: Device type where the impression was shown.

Name: ExternalConversionSource
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Other
WEBPAGE / Website
ANALYTICS / Analytics
UPLOAD / Import from clicks
AD_CALL_METRICS / Calls from ads
OFFERS / Offers
ENGAGEMENT / Engagement ads
WEBSITE_CALL_METRICS / Calls from website
STORE_VISITS / Store visits
ANDROID_IN_APP / Android in-app action
ANDROID_DOWNLOAD / Android app install (from Google Play)
IOS_IN_APP / iOS in-app action
IOS_FIRST_OPEN / iOS app install (first open)
APP_UNSPECIFIED / Mobile app
ANDROID_FIRST_OPEN / Android app install (first open)
UPLOAD_CALLS / Import from calls
FIREBASE / Firebase
CLICK_TO_CALL / Phone number clicks
SALESFORCE / Salesforce.com
STORE_SALES_CRM / Store sales (data partner)
STORE_SALES_PAYMENT_NETWORK / Store sales (payment network)
GOOGLE_PLAY / Google Play
Notes: The source of conversion such as website, import from calls.

Name: ExternalCustomerId
Notes: The Customer ID.

Name: HourOfDay
Notes: The hour of day as a number between 0 and 23, inclusive.

Name: Id
Notes: ID of the main object of this row.

Name: Impressions
Notes: Count of how often your ad has appeared on a search results page or website on the Google Network.

Name: Month
Notes: The first day of the month, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: MonthOfYear
Enum Values:
JANUARY / January
FEBRUARY / February
MARCH / March
APRIL / April
MAY / May
JUNE / June
JULY / July
AUGUST / August
SEPTEMBER / September
OCTOBER / October
NOVEMBER / November
DECEMBER / December
Notes: The name of the month of the year, e.g., "December".

Name: Name
Notes: The name of the main object in this row. For example, in a Campaign Performance Report this will be the name of each row's Campaign. In an Ad Group Performance Report this will be the name of each row's AdGroup.

Name: NonRemovedAdGroupCount
Notes: The count of non-removed ad groups using the bidding strategy.

Name: NonRemovedAdGroupCriteriaCount
Notes: The count of non-removed ad group criteria using the bidding strategy.

Name: NonRemovedCampaignCount
Notes: The count of non-removed campaigns using the bidding strategy.

Name: PageOnePromotedBidCeiling
Notes: Maximum bid limit for the PageOnePromotedBiddingScheme.

Name: PageOnePromotedBidChangesForRaisesOnly
Notes: Whether the PageOnePromoted strategy always follows bid estimate changes (false), or only increases (true).

Name: PageOnePromotedBidModifier
Notes: Bid multiplier defined on the PageOnePromotedBiddingScheme. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: PageOnePromotedRaiseBidWhenBudgetConstrained
Notes: Whether the PageOnePromoted strategy is allowed to raise bids if the campaign is "Limited by budget".

Name: PageOnePromotedRaiseBidWhenLowQualityScore
Display Name: Low quality keywords (Target search page location)
Notes: Whether the PageOnePromoted strategy is allowed to raise bids on keywords with lower-range quality scores.

Name: PageOnePromotedStrategyGoal
Notes: Strategy goal of where impressions will show on search result pages.

Name: Quarter
Notes: The first day of the quarter, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd. Uses the calendar year for quarters, e.g., the second quarter of 2014 starts on 2014-04-01.

Name: Status
Enum Values:
ENABLED / Enabled
REMOVED / Removed
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: The status of the main object in this row. For example, in a Campaign Performance Report this will be the status of each row's Campaign. In an Ad Group Performance Report this will be the status of each row's AdGroup.

Name: SystemStatus
Enum Values:
UNKNOWN / Unknown
UNCONSTRAINED / Not limited
LEARNING_NEW / Learning (new strategy or reactivated strategy)
LEARNING_SETTING_CHANGE / Learning (setting change)
LEARNING_BUDGET_CHANGE / Learning (budget change)
LEARNING_COMPOSITION_CHANGE / Learning (keywords added or removed)
LEARNING_CONVERSION_TYPE_CHANGE / Learning (conversion type change)
LEARNING_CONVERSION_SETTING_CHANGE / Learning (conversion setting change)
LIMITED_BY_BID_CONSTRAINTS / Limited (bid constraints)
LIMITED_BY_MAX_BID_LIMIT / Limited (bid ceiling)
LIMITED_BY_MIN_BID_LIMIT / Limited (bid floor)
LIMITED_BY_MIN_ROAS_LIMIT / Limited (min ROAS)
LIMITED_BY_DATA / Limited (not enough data)
LIMITED_BY_BUDGET / Limited (budget constrained)
LIMITED_BY_LOW_PRIORITY_SPEND / Limited (low priority spend)
LIMITED_BY_LOW_QUALITY / Limited (low Quality Score)
MISCONFIGURED_CONVERSION_TYPES / Misconfigured (conversion types)
MISCONFIGURED_CONVERSION_SETTINGS / Misconfigured (conversion settings)
INACTIVE / Inactive
UNAVAILABLE / Unavailable
MULTIPLE_LEARNING / Multiple (learning)
MULTIPLE_LIMITED / Multiple (limited)
MULTIPLE_MISCONFIGURED / Multiple (misconfigured)
MULTIPLE / Multiple
Notes: The status of bidding strategy system.

Name: TargetCpa
Notes: The average CPA target set on the Target CPA bidding strategy.

Name: TargetCpaMaxCpcBidCeiling
Notes: The maximum CPC bid limit for the Target CPA bidding strategy.

Name: TargetCpaMaxCpcBidFloor
Notes: The minimum CPC bid limit for the Target CPA bidding strategy.

Name: TargetOutrankShare
Notes: Target fraction (in micros) of auctions where the advertiser should outrank the competitor.

Name: TargetOutrankShareBidChangesForRaisesOnly
Notes: Whether the TargetRoas strategy always follows bid estimate changes (false), or only increases (true).

Name: TargetOutrankShareCompetitorDomain
Notes: The competitor's visible domain URL for the TargetRoas strategy.

Name: TargetOutrankShareMaxCpcBidCeiling
Display Name: Upper Max Cpc Bid limit (Target Outranking Share)
Notes: The TargetRoas strategy's ceiling on max CPC bids.

Name: TargetOutrankShareRaiseBidWhenLowQualityScore
Notes: Whether the TargetRoas strategy is allowed to raise bids on keywords with lower-range quality scores.

Name: TargetRoas
Notes: The desired revenue (based on conversion data) per unit of spend for the TargetRoas BiddingStrategyConfiguration. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: TargetRoasBidCeiling
Notes: Maximum bid limit that applies to all keywords managed by the TargetRoas BiddingStrategyConfiguration.

Name: TargetRoasBidFloor
Notes: Minimum bid limit that applies to all keywords managed by the TargetRoas BiddingStrategyConfiguration.

Name: TargetSpendBidCeiling
Notes: The largest max CPC bid that can be set by the TargetSpend BiddingStrategyConfiguration.

Name: TargetSpendSpendTarget
Notes: The spend target under which to maximize clicks. Specified by the TargetSpend BiddingStrategyConfiguration.

Name: Type
Enum Values:
BUDGET_OPTIMIZER / auto
CONVERSION_OPTIMIZER / max/target cpa
MANUAL_CPC / cpc
MANUAL_CPV / cpv
MANUAL_CPM / cpm
PAGE_ONE_PROMOTED / Target search page location
TARGET_SPEND / Maximize clicks
ENHANCED_CPC / Enhanced CPC
TARGET_CPA / Target CPA
TARGET_ROAS / Target ROAS
TARGET_OUTRANK_SHARE / Target Outranking Share
NONE / None
UNKNOWN / unknown
Notes: The type of the main object in this row. For example, in a Bid Goal Performance Report this will be the type of the BiddingStrategyConfiguration. In a Shared Set Report this will be the type of the SharedSet.

Name: ValuePerAllConversion
Notes: The value, on average, of all conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ValuePerConversion
Notes: The total value of your conversions divided by the total number of conversions. To prevent calculation accuracy issues, fields whose data type is Double can be used only with the following operators in predicates: LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN. This is also true for AWQL: Only the operators < and > are allowed in the WHERE clause.

Name: ViewThroughConversions
Notes: The total number of view-through conversions. These happen when a customer sees an image or rich media ad, then later completes a conversion on your site without interacting with (e.g. clicking on) another ad.

Name: Week
Notes: The date for the Monday of the week, formatted as yyyy-MM-dd.

Name: Year
Notes: The year, formatted as yyyy.
